  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Assistant0",
      "description": "# Running Assistant0 for the first time\n\nAssistant0 is built in NextJS and already has all the dependencies installed for you to start using it, including the the [Auth0 NextJS SDK](https://auth0.com/docs/quickstart/webapp/nextjs/01-login#install-the-auth0-next-js-sdk) to take care of auth for you.\n\nFor the GenAI portion we are going to use [LangGraph](https://www.langchain.com/langgraph).\n\nBefore we can run the application, we need to verify that our app's `.env` file is set up properly."
    },
    {
      "file": "auth0-assistant0/.env",
      "description": "## Auth0 .env variables\n\n>Notice that `./auth0-assistant/.env` has been opened for you above.\n\nThe Auth0 Labs extension pulled down the values for you when it generated the .env. *Optionally*, you can verify that these are correct against your Auth0 dashboard by visiting the **Settings** tab of your My Oktane App.\n\nYou'll still need to configure your app's base URL and your OpenAI API key. We'll do that next.\n\n",
      "line": 7,
      "selection": {
        "start": {
          "line": 4,
          "character": 1
        },
        "end": {
          "line": 7,
          "character": 35
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "title": "Update `.env` - Set the app base URL",
      "file": "auth0-assistant0/.env",
      "description": "## Update `.env` - Set the app base URL\n\nIn order to configure the app to work properly in the Codespace you need to set the base URL.\n\n1. [Select this link](command:codetour.sendTextToTerminal?[\"echo https://$CODESPACE_NAME-3000.app.github.dev/\"]) to run the command on the terminal.\n\n2. Copy the output and update the `APP_BASE_URL` with that value.\n\n-----\n\nAfter the update your APP_BASE_URL should look something like this:\n\n```\nAPP_BASE_URL=\"https://humble-winner-74xv5jxw462r9pv-3000.app.github.dev/\"\n```",
      "line": 3,
      "selection": {
        "start": {
          "line": 3,
          "character": 14
        },
        "end": {
          "line": 3,
          "character": 38
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "file": "auth0-assistant0/.env",
      "description": "## Update `.env` - generate an application secret\n\nNow let's generate a secret to encode the values.\n\n1. Select [this link](command:codetour.sendTextToTerminal?[\"openssl rand -hex 32\"]) to run the command `openssl rand -hex 32` in the terminal.\n\n2. Copy the output and update the value of the `AUTH0_SECRET` variable highlighted on the line above.",
      "line": 2,
      "selection": {
        "start": {
          "line": 2,
          "character": 14
        },
        "end": {
          "line": 2,
          "character": 70
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "title": "Set up - OpenAI API Key",
      "file": "auth0-assistant0/.env",
      "description": "## OpenAI API Key\n> If you closed your OpenAI tab, [log back in](https://auth.openai.com/log-in).\n\n1. From your OpenAI account, [create an API key](https://platform.openai.com/api-keys).\n2. Copy the value of this API key.\n2. Update the `OPENAI_API_KEY` variable on the highlighted line above by pasting the value of your API key.\n\n>This will allow your assistant to use the OpenAI models.",
      "line": 1,
      "selection": {
        "start": {
          "line": 1,
          "character": 16
        },
        "end": {
          "line": 1,
          "character": 29
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "title": "Understanding the code",
      "description": "## Understanding the code\n\nThis is the application structure:\n\n- `src/app`: Contains the Next.js application routes, layout, and pages.\n- `src/app/page.tsx`: Home page with chat interface.\n- `src/app/api/chat/route.ts`: API route for handling chat requests. This is where the AI agent is defined.\n- `src/components`: UI components used in the application.\n- `src/lib`: Services and configurations. This is where custom tools will be defined.\n- `src/utils`: Utility functions\n- `.env`: File to hold the environment variables"
    },
    {
      "title": "Running the app",
      "description": "## Running Assistant0 for the first time\n\n1. Select [this link](command:workbench.action.debug.start) to run the application. \n\n1. Select the **Open in Browser** in the dialog that appears in the bottom right corner to visit your app's URL. \n>If you miss the dialog, you can always select the **PORTS** tab below next to **TERMINAL** and then hover over the **FORWARDED ADDRESS** and select the globe icon to open your app's URL.\n\n1. Sign up for the application.\n1. Once logged in, try asking it *\"What can you help me with?\"*\n\n*Tip: on the first try it might take a while for the Assistant to respond to you. Look for the the `POST /api/chat` call in the terminal to know that everything is functioning as expected*",
      "selection": {
        "start": {
          "line": 6,
          "character": 119
        },
        "end": {
          "line": 6,
          "character": 136
        }
      }
    }
